Accolades include the Bernard/Ebb Songwriting Awards Grand Prize, multiple Washington Area Music Awards (pop/rock vocalist 2014, pop/rock album 2014 for his album Twelve Stories, pop/rock instrumentalist 2014, and pop/rock vocalist 2015), and mentions and features in national media outlets such as the Washington Post, the Huffington Post, and the Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon. Elements of Owen’s music have been likened to that of Paul Simon, James Taylor, John Mayer, and the Wallflowers, among others – though the end result is all his own.
